flowRoot.flowPara: The inventor of the programming language Smalltalk was the first who used objects in software development. It's the first Programming Language that was called "Object Oriented Programming Language". Like Gutenberg could print complete books with the letters in his printing press you can create biger things out of such objects. A Class is a single part of a complete software product. Eg. in an addressbook Class you would have predefined fileds for Name, Address, Phone Number...". You can also have such templates in Psychology, Mechanic, ...
Simplification / standardisation through predefined (software) templates makes things more efficient but people maybe loose base skills when only using templates
